ions et les stratégies communes des deux colonies, compare les Quatre-vingt-douze Résolutions et le Seventh Report et dévoile les raisons de l’inaccomplissement d’un projet d’émancipation coloniale à la fois semblable et différent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9782763758602?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782763758602423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782763758602/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles